  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nwhen syncing from scratch with bonsai tree and X_CHECKPOINT, I always get to a point after a few hours where it logs\r\n\r\n`INFO  | FastSyncTargetManager | Best peer 0x459cdebf7d99d644e7 has chain height 16024176 below pivotBlock height 16030869`\r\n\r\nand keeps printing it without ever exiting from it (let it go for 2-3 hours twice). The block sync doesn't continue when this message appears.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** My guess is that the client should select another peer and continue from there, even if it's not the best (?)\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** About 4-6 times during a fresh sync from start.\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: hyperledger/besu:22.10.0 running on Docker compose\r\n* OS Name & Version: Ubuntu 22.04.1 LTS\r\n* Kernel Version: linux 5.15.0-53-generic\r\n* Docker Version: 20.10.21\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: own built, AMD Ryzen 5 2600 Six-Core Processor, 32GB RAM, 2TB nVME\r\n",
